title: For Sale/Trade:  Spikes Tactical ST15 AR-15 w/extras - Sale/Trade
postcontent:
Up for your consideration is my Spikes Tactical ST15 .223/5.56 NATO 16" Milspec barrel w/1:7 twist... with several tasteful additions and several 30 round mags.  I've owned this gun for about a year and enjoyed every second of it.  I've literally only put about 100 rounds through her total and kept her in immaculate condition.  I firm believe Spikes makes the absolute best AR for the money being made in the USA with high end, well built parts.  Below are some of the modifications professionally performed:

- KNS anti-roation pins
- Rainier Arms - phase 5 - tactical extended bolt release v2
- Yankee Hill Machine full vertical/horizontal rail and hand guard system
- Noveske KX3 Flash Suppressor 
- Spikes Tactical Battle trigger
- 1x Sight Mark holographic scope with side laser (unmounted pressure plate)
- Troy Pop Ups
- Currently pictured with a line wrapped buffer for the minimalist however I'll likely throw on a Magpul six position stock shortly.

She shoots like a dream and she should.  I spent more than $1,600 without tax getting some of the various options I wanted.  The scope is nothing to brag about obviously but for $150 new, it is about the best I've found so far.  Below is a link directly to the base ST15 which I purchased before doing all the additions.

http://www.spikestactical.com/st15-16-midlength-le-carbine-p-443.html
http://www.majorpandemic.com/2011/08/spikes-tactical-st-15-mid-length-ar15m4.html
Link above has all specs and a thorough independent review.

Ideally, I'm looking for a good trade however would entertain a cash offer.  If you can find them in stock on the web you'll pay about $850 plus the obvious transfer fees and minus any of the additions.  I'm looking for roughly that out of it which would be a stellar deal at half the price - considering all the additions.  For trade - I'd give preference to a Colt Defender, Kimber compact variants or any higher end compact 1911.  I can add cash for the right deal.  Considering I by no means have tried every semi there is out there I would also entertain various other offers so send over your trade offer.  The worse either party can say is "no".
